# MiniProject

## How to Run This Project
Follow the steps below to run the project on your local machine.

---### 1. Clone the Repository```
git clone https://github.com/Das-R10/MiniProject.git
cd MiniProject
```

---### 2. Create a Virtual Environment```
python -m venv venv
```
Activate the virtual environment:
For Windows:
```venv\Scripts\activate
```
For macOS / Linux:
```source venv/bin/activate
```

### 3. Install Dependencies
Make sure `requirements.txt` exists, then run:
```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 4. Run the Project
If this is a FastAPI project:
```
uvicorn main:app --reload
```
Then open in your browser:
```
http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

API documentation:

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
```
---
If this is a normal Python script:
```
python main.py
```
(Replace `main.py` with your actual file name if different.)
---


* Always use a virtual environment before installing dependencies.
* Recommended Python version: 3.10 or higher.

---

If you tell me your exact main file name (like `app.py`, `server.py`, etc.), I can customize this perfectly for your project.
